Created `src/utils/http.ts`. The `<T>` generic propagates to the return type so callers get typed responses:

```ts
const user = await http.get<User>('/api/users/123');
// user is typed as User, not unknown

const newUser = await http.post<User>('/api/users', { name: 'Alice', email: 'a@b.com' });
```

`AbortController` with a timeout is important — `fetch` has no built-in timeout. Without this, a slow server can hold your connection open indefinitely. The `finally` block always clears the timer to avoid leaking it when the request completes normally.

`new URLSearchParams` safely encodes query parameters — manually building query strings with string concatenation can break with special characters or create injection vectors.

