Created `src/utils/observable.ts`. The observer pattern decouples the thing that changes from the things that react to it. Subscribers don't know about each other.

Returning an unsubscribe function from `subscribe()` is the modern pattern — callers hold the cleanup function and invoke it to stop receiving updates, without needing to keep a reference to the original observer.

The `derived` function creates a computed projection:
```ts
const count = new Observable(0);
const doubled = derived(count, n => n * 2);
count.set(5);
console.log(doubled.value); // 10
